thread.title: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks
thread.title_full: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks - The Denver Post

author: The Associated Press
title: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks
text:
The following list represents the most streamed tracks on Spotify, based on the number of people who shared it divided by the number who listened to it, from Friday July 24 to Thursday, July 30 via Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and Spotify.
UNITED STATES
1. The Weeknd, "Can't Feel My Face" (Republic Records)
2. OMI, "Cheerleader - Felix Jaehn Remix Radio Edit" (Ultra Records)
3. The Weeknd, "The Hills" (Republic Records)
4. Fetty Wap, "679 (feat. Remy Boyz)" (300 Entertainment)
5. Major Lazer, "Lean On (feat. MØ & DJ Snake)" (Mad Decent)
6. Selena Gomez, "Good For You" (Interscope Records)
7. Fetty Wap, "Trap Queen" (300 Entertainment)
8. Jack Ü,Skrillex,Diplo, "Where Are Ü Now (with Justin Bieber)" (Atlantic Records)
9. Silento, "Watch Me (Whip / Nae Nae)" (Island Records)
10. Wiz Khalifa, "See You Again (feat. Charlie Puth)" (Atlantic Records)
UNITED KINGDOM
1. Lost Frequencies, "Are You with Me - Radio Edit" (Ultra Records)
2. Major Lazer, "Lean On (feat. MØ & DJ Snake)" (Mad Decent)
3. Little Mix, "Black Magic" (Sony Music Entertainment UK Limited)
4. OMI, "Cheerleader - Felix Jaehn Remix Radio Edit" (Ultra Records)
5. Walk the Moon, "Shut Up and Dance" (RCA Records)
6. Fetty Wap, "Trap Queen" (300 Entertainment)
